<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-12-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="269" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Barrett</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-12-20"><hi rend="italic">December 20,
                                    1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Barrett reports that an official announcement has been made of the
                            discovery of a plot to dispose of the President of Colombia and to
                            organize a new government. Many prominent men who were arrested are now
                            about to undergo trial by court-matrial. Among the leaders are a former
                            cabinet minister and generals.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>